{"id": "duc04-testb-26:6#20", "contents": "Speakers at the conference shared personal experiences and insights into the complexities of human behavior during times of conflict. Ginn Fourie, a physiotherapist who lost her daughter in a 1993 attack, spoke about the importance of helping those who were compelled to do wrong due to their circumstances. She shared her experience of attending the amnesty hearings of her daughter's killers and supporting their bid for freedom. Fourie's emotional appeal for understanding and reconciliation earned her a standing ovation, emphasizing the need for healing and reconciliation in South Africa."}
